For most, it's not an end but the beginning of something new. This is the awakening of a generation to the opportunities that lie ahead. Research has shown that people in their fifties are more vital now than they were only 10 years ago. Contact St. Louis County Library by phone 314-994-3300 or visit www.slcl.org. Jane Pauley has been a familiar face on TV for more than 30 years. She served as co-host of Today from 1976 to 1989, anchored Dateline NBC for 11 years, and in 2004 became the host of her own daytime program, The Jane Pauley Show. Her memoir, "Skywriting: A Life Out of the Blue," was a New York Times bestseller. Jane is not an advice giver but a storyteller. Here she tells her own story and introduces readers to the fascinating people she has featured on her award-winning Today show segment, "Life Reimagined Today." You'll meet Betsy McCarthy, who traded in her executive briefcase for knitting needles; Gid Pool,
